Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: Differential cross sections of neutron scattering on N-14 at energies between 7.89 MeV and 13.85 MeV

x4freetext: Differential cross sections of neutron scattering
on N-14 at energies between 7.89 MeV and 13.85 MeV
Deuterium gas target, 1.0 cm in diam. and
3.0 cm in length, gas pressure 0.19-0.20 mPa.
Mean neutron energy is defined within +/- 20 keV.
N/Gamma Discrimination with Pulse Shape Analysis.
Detectors located behind a massive collimator shielding
in a distance of 1200 cm from the sample. The angle
separation between the detectors is 12.5 deg.
The angle region covered is 12.5 deg to 160 deg.
an additional NE213 detector was used as relative
fluence monitor, diam. 3.81 cm, length 3.81 cm.
The movable monitor (in a fixed distance of 651 cm)
was always in a position of 58.9 deg relative
17.5 cm from the gas target centre.
Monte Carlo simulated TOF spectra of the complete
angular distribution were iteratively adjusted to
the measured TOF spectra. The simulation comprised
the neutron production in the gas target and the
scattering geometry between target, sample and
Simulation of the scattering on silicon was carried
out with the results obtained under same conditions
Total errors comprise counting statistics and
contain an additional uncertainty component of
between 1.2% and 17% in order to consider the
influence of the chosen maximum order l-max
of the fitted Legendre polynomial on the integral
Cross sections were extracted based on the assumption
are available upon request from the authors
Tabulated data (partly) are given in PTB-N-44.
SD: Meaningless zeros were deleted from
the data. EN-RSL-HW -> EN-RSL-FW in Subents 002-021.
SD: ERR-2 -> ANG-ERR in COMMON section.
